					<p>
			A <term>cold advisory</term> is issued whenever the wind chill falls below 0<m>^\circ</m>F. How fast does the wind need to be at an air temperature of 10<m>^\circ</m>F to issue a cold advisory?
		</p>
			</li>

			<li>
					<p>
			Between a wind chill of 0<m>^\circ</m>F and -15<m>^\circ</m>F, schools in our district are open but kids may not go outside for recess. What is the corresponding range of wind speeds at an air temperature of 10<m>^\circ</m>F?
		</p>
